# Codex Ideas for Fish Config

This file summarizes possible improvements I noticed during a quick scan of your Fish config. These are optional and meant as ideas.

## Ideas

- Make `fastfetch` use an absolute config path so it works no matter where the shell starts.
  - Example: `fastfetch -c ~/.config/fastfetch/examples/6.jsonc`
  - Location: `config.fish`

- Guard optional tools in `conf.d/*.fish` so missing binaries do not spam errors at startup.
  - Example pattern:
    - `type -q fzf; and fzf --fish | source`
    - `type -q starship; and starship init fish | source`
    - `type -q zoxide; and zoxide init fish | source`
    - `test -f "$HOME/.cargo/env.fish"; and source "$HOME/.cargo/env.fish"`

- Make `EDITOR` fallback more robust if `nvim` is not installed.
  - Example:
    - `set -l editor (command -s nvim; or command -s vim; or command -s vi)`
    - `set -gx EDITOR $editor`
    - `set -gx VISUAL $EDITOR`
    - `set -gx SUDO_EDITOR $EDITOR`
  - Location: `conf.d/set.fish`

- Avoid odd behavior in `mansec` when `fzf` is canceled.
  - Example:
    - `test -n "$sec"; or return 1`
  - Location: `functions/mansec.fish`

- Consider `command` prefix for wrappers where you do not want functions/aliases to recurse.
  - Example: `command ls` inside custom wrappers or where you rely on the external binary.

## Notes

- These are optional; nothing is broken, just quality-of-life improvements.
- If you want, I can apply any of the changes above.
